work of criticism. He sets each poem in the context of the work as a whole and defines the poems' major symbols. Also included are an introduction and a bibliography.Publication of this collection is a major literary event in the English-speaking world: here at last is the work of a major figure, masterfully translated.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  aa negress.  aaesthetics.  aalms.  aanguish.  aapparition.  abilingual.  acanon.  aclassics.  acoup de des.  afiction.  afrench literature.  afrench poetry.  afrench poets.  afutile petition.  agift of the poem.  ala pleiade.  aliterature.  amodern literature.  amodernism.  apoetry collection.  apoetry.  arenewal.  asalut.  asalutation.  asea breeze.  asigh.  asummer sadness.  asurrealism.  asymbolism.  athe azure.  athe bell ringer.  athe clown chastised.  athe contemporary parnassus.  athe flowers.  athe jinx.  athe satirical parnassus.  athe windows.  aweary of bitter sleep.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094811240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948112423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948112/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles